This paper discusses the issue of URI canonicalization and its impact on accurately counting Mementos (archival web captures). This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), web technologies (cs.WEB), cybersecurity (cs.CR), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). However, given the focus on web archiving and URI canonicalization, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.WEB, cs.CR, and cs.HC.
